<h1 id=3D"expgalaxybeneficiaryv1-Capability:Createbeneficiary"><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"><strong>Capability: Create beneficiary&nbsp;</=
strong></span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxybeneficiaryv1-POST/beneficiaryCreate">POST /<span data-t=
eams=3D"true">beneficiaryCreate</span></h2>
<p>This endpoint creates a new beneficiary as provided in request body.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><u><strong>Feb 2026 Changes as part=
 of Divisions:</strong></u></span> DivisionId is included as part of the ad=
d beneficiary request body so that the same can be persisted in PDP when IR=
OM API gets called from the Beneficiary INF API. Refer to the SD here for t=
he sequence flow details: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/=
display/ARTC/SD%3A+Sub-Orgs%28Divisions%29+Channels#SD:SubOrgs(Divisions)Ch=
annels-Beneficiary-Addbeneficiary" rel=3D"nofollow">SD: Sub-Orgs(Divisions)=
 Channels - Beneficiary-Addbeneficiary</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><u><strong>May 2026 ERM changes ass=
ociated with Confirmation of Payee:</strong></u></span><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0=
,0);">As part of CoP feature, if CoP validation is performed by a maker whe=
n adding a BSB &amp; account no beneficiary, the CoP validation matched sta=
tus Outcome should be included as part of the EXP API request so that the C=
oP validation outcome can be displayed in the beneficiary details authorisa=
tion screen. Refer to the SD here for details:</span><span style=3D"color: =
rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><a href=3D"https://confluence.srv=
.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/06+-+SD%3A+Confirmation+of+payee#id-06SD:Confi=
rmationofpayee-Sequenceflowdiagram" rel=3D"nofollow">06 - SD: Confirmation =
of payee - Sequenceflowdiagram</a></p>
<p><br></p>
