<h1 id=3D"expgalaxybeneficiaryv1-Capability:AliaslookupAPI"><span style=3D"=
color: rgb(51,102,255);"><strong>Capability:<span class=3D"fabric-text-colo=
r-mark"> Alias lookup API</span></strong></span></h1>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxybeneficiaryv1-POST/aliasLookup"><span>POST /<span style=
=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">aliasLookup</span></span></h2>
<p>This endpoint does an alias lookup by calling the payment alias lookup e=
ndpoint. (<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/co=
mponents/apis/payment-alias-resolution-v2" rel=3D"nofollow">https://mesh.we=
stpac.com.au/components/apis/payment-alias-resolution-v2</a>)&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-moved">AUG 25</span>=
 <span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">The EXP API maintains the session l=
imit (50) and get current count from the INF API </span><a style=3D"letter-=
spacing: 0.0px;" href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC=
/inf-payment-utils-v1#infpaymentutilsv1-Capability:Checkcounterlimit" rel=
=3D"nofollow">inf-payment-utils-v1 - Westpac One Core - Westpac Enterprise =
Confluence</a><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">, and the EXP API also=
 triggers the limit increases after successful triggering.&nbsp;</span><a s=
tyle=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;" href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.=
au/display/ARTC/inf-payment-utils-v1#infpaymentutilsv1-Capability:Increases=
counterlimit" rel=3D"nofollow">inf-payment-utils-v1 - Westpac One Core - We=
stpac Enterprise Confluence</a></p>
<p>It's the temporary solution to fulfill the requirement BR.10 in <a href=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/ART-9715%3A+Detailed=
+Requirements" rel=3D"nofollow">ART-9715: Detailed Requirements - Westpac O=
ne Core - Westpac Enterprise Confluence</a></p>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge">NOV 25</span> SAFI integration =
with the existing endpoint is expected. Addition parameters for identifying=
 the caller action may be required. (e.g. Add Beneficiary / Update Benefici=
ary) End to end flow refer to the SD: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.wes=
tpac.com.au/display/ARTC/05.+SD%3A+SAFI+integration+for+PayID+resolution+li=
mit" rel=3D"nofollow">05. SD: SAFI integration for PayID resolution limit -=
 Westpac One Core - Westpac Enterprise Confluence</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-1001040020" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-1001040020" c=
