<h1 id=3D"expgalaxybeneficiaryv1-Capability:Tovalidatetheconfirmationofpaye=
ewhenaddingorupdatingabeneficiary(May2026ERM)"><span style=3D"color: rgb(51=
,102,255);"><strong>Capability:<span class=3D"fabric-text-color-mark"><span=
>&nbsp;</span>To validate the confirmation of payee when adding or updating=
 a beneficiary (May 2026 ERM)</span></strong></span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxybeneficiaryv1-POST/accountNameCheck"><span>POST /account=
NameCheck</span></h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">This endpoint validates the custom=
er name for both, On-Us or Off-us scenarios.</span></p>
<p>Integration/Orchestration: <span>The endpoint will consume the following=
 APIs,</span></p>
<ol>
<li>The CoP Daily limit and Session limit static values will be configured =
and maintained in the EXP API config</li>
<li><p><strong>channel-payment-utils-v1 API</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>GET /payment/counters/{name}/customers/{customerId}</code><br>
 =E2=86=92 Used to validate whether the CoP daily limit has reached for a u=
ser.</li>
<li><code>GET /payment/counters/{name}/customers/sessions/{sessionId}</code=
><br>
 =E2=86=92 Used to validate whether the CoP session limit has reached for a=
 user.</li>
<li><code>POST /payment/counters/{name}/customers/{customerId}/sessions/{se=
ssionId}</code><br>
 =E2=86=92 Used to increment the CoP daily counter &amp; session counter if=
 the limits have not yet been reached.</li>
<li><code>POST /payment/counters/{name}/customers/{customerId}</code><br>
 =E2=86=92 Used to increment the CoP daily counter if the limits have not y=
et been reached.</li>
</ul></li>
<li><p><strong>payee-services-v1 API</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>POST /accountNameCheck</code><br>
 =E2=86=92 Used to validate the payee name as part of the CoP process.</li>
</ul></li>
<li><strong>Send Custom Fact("PAYEE_NAME_CHECK_COLOUR") to SAFI</strong>
<ul>
<li>Custom fact to SAFI will go via <em>cap-custsvcmgt-custsecyverifctn-ada=
ptvauth-v2</em><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>CAP=
 API<span>&nbsp;</span></span><em>POST /analyse</em><span style=3D"color: r=
gb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>endpoint<span>&nbsp;</span></span><s>Enti=
tlements using "mep-node/framework-otp-provider-addon" MESH JS Library</s>.=
<s> Implementation reference can be found here:<span style=3D"letter-spacin=
g: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://bitbucke=
t.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/galaxy-beneficiary-microfrontend/br=
owse/api/server/api/controllers/postAliasLookupController.ts?at=3Drefs%2Fhe=
ads%2Ffeature%2FART-58608-safi-payid-lookup-2#112" rel=3D"nofollow">Source =
of postAliasLookupController.ts - safi-payid-lookup-2#112</a></s></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">This endpoint will be used in the =
following flow: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/AR=
TC/06+-+SD%3A+Confirmation+of+payee" rel=3D"nofollow">06 - SD: Confirmation=
