</div>
<p><br></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Send Custom Fact("PAYEE_NAME_CHECK_COLOUR") to SAFI</strong>&nb=
sp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style=3D"list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>To send the custom fact to SAFI,&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,7=
7);">Channels will consume<span>&nbsp;</span></span><em>cap-custsvcmgt-cust=
secyverifctn-adaptvauth-v2</em><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>=
&nbsp;</span>CAP API<span>&nbsp;</span></span><em>POST /analyse</em><span s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>endpoint(<a href=3D"https=
://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/cap-custsvcmgt-custsecyverifctn-adap=
tvauth-v2?tab=3Dcontract#tag/Analyse/operation/analyse" class=3D"external-l=
ink" rel=3D"nofollow">cap-custsvcmgt-custsecyverifctn-adaptvauth-v2 - POST =
/analyse</a>) </span><s>use the MESH JS library (<strong><code>mep-node/fra=
mework-otp-provider-addon</code></strong>), specifically the <strong><code>=
OtpProvider.analyse</code></strong> function, which transmits custom fact d=
etails to SAFI via Entitlements</s>. <s>Please refer to the implementation =
details here for reference: <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au=
/projects/WDP/repos/galaxy-beneficiary-microfrontend/browse/api/server/api/=
controllers/postAliasLookupController.ts?at=3Drefs%2Fheads%2Ffeature%2FART-=
58608-safi-payid-lookup#133" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Sourc=
e of postAliasLookupController.ts - safi-payid-lookup#133</a></s>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">CAP API Request Body</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">For "eventType", d</span>epending on=
 where in the flow a bene can be added/updated, one of the following should=
 be set=20
<ul>
<li><span>ADD_PAYEE-BENEFICIARY</span></li>
<li><span>EDIT_PAYEE-BENEFICIARY</span><span>&nbsp;</span></li>
<li><span>PAYMENT</span></li>
</ul></li>
<li><span>"eventMetaData" object will be constructed as below,</span></li>
<li>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
